---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Badge · Porchlight">
  <h1>Badge</h1>
  <p>
    A compact label for statuses, counts, and tags. Inline-flex pill; tones via
    <code>[data-tone]</code>. Status tones consume the WCAG-AA
    <code>-bg</code>/<code>-text</code> token pairs, so they're legible in both
    themes by construction.
  </p>

  <h2>Tones</h2>
  <div class="c-badge-group row">
    <span class="c-badge">Default</span>
    <span class="c-badge" data-tone="accent">New</span>
    <span class="c-badge" data-tone="success">Active</span>
    <span class="c-badge" data-tone="warning">Pending review</span>
    <span class="c-badge" data-tone="danger">Blocked</span>
  </div>

  <h2>With a leading dot</h2>
  <p>A status pip for at-a-glance scanning.</p>
  <div class="c-badge-group row">
    <span class="c-badge" data-tone="success"><span class="c-badge__dot"></span>Online</span>
    <span class="c-badge" data-tone="warning"><span class="c-badge__dot"></span>Degraded</span>
    <span class="c-badge" data-tone="danger"><span class="c-badge__dot"></span>Outage</span>
  </div>

  <h2>Groups</h2>
  <p>Use <code>.c-badge-group</code> for wrapping sets of status badges.</p>
  <div class="c-badge-group row">
    <span class="c-badge">Inbound</span>
    <span class="c-badge" data-tone="accent">New</span>
    <span class="c-badge" data-tone="warning">SLA watch</span>
    <span class="c-badge" data-tone="success">Routable</span>
  </div>

  <h2>In context</h2>
  <p>Badges pair naturally with table cells, list items, and headers.</p>
  <div class="context">
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Account</th><th>Status</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Acme Ops</td><td><span class="c-badge" data-tone="success">Active</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td>Northwind</td><td><span class="c-badge" data-tone="warning">Trialing</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td>Globex</td><td><span class="c-badge" data-tone="danger">Past due</span></td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .row {
    margin-block-end: var(--pl-space-5);
  }
  .context {
    padding: var(--pl-space-4);
    background: var(--pl-color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--pl-color-border);
    border-radius: var(--pl-radius-lg);
  }
  .context table {
    inline-size: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
  }
  .context :where(th, td) {
    padding: var(--pl-space-2) var(--pl-space-3);
    border-block-end: 1px solid var(--pl-color-border);
    text-align: start;
  }
  .context th {
    color: var(--pl-color-text-muted);
    font-size: var(--pl-text-sm);
  }
</style>
